If you try to get servlet name in any servlet constructor 
with "this.getServletName()" you will get a NullPointerException at 
javax.servlet.GenericServlet.getServletName(GenericServlet.java:366)

   For example in servlet constructor I tried to prepare an init message and 
send to log in init() method;

   public TestServlet() {
        initMsg = new StringBuffer();
--->    initMsg.append(this.getServletName()).append(" initialized.");
   }

   public void init() throws ServletException {
       this.log(initMsg.toString());
   }

   I tried same servlet with Resin 3.0.4 It worked fine.
Good luck,

Mr.Sea
